cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the analysis of Internet infrastructure and the utilization of IPv4 address space. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the analysis of data and the development of methodologies, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
